BBC's "Sherlock" captures the essence of Conan Doyle's character and stories. They are frightening, enthralling, captivating, and impossible to turn away from. The performances are simply unparalleled in television today. On the surface, the mysterious aspects of the story lines are incredibly satisfying. But the real beauty of the show lies in its deeper, inexplicit aspects. The looks on John's face as the mystery dives into the fantastic. Sherlock's utter disregard for personal relationships outside of John, Lestrade, Mycroft, and Mrs. Hudson. 

Long story short? This show will find its way to your all-time favorite list. And It will not leave.